Sentencas: Cobalt-free ferrites are attracting tremendous spotlight as prospective solid oxide fuel cell cathode material nowadays owing to their good structural stability and great thermo-mechanical compatibility with electrolytes.
Titulo: Utilization of an Isovalent Doping Strategy in Cobalt-Free Ferrites for Highly Active and Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: Nevertheless, the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity for cobalt-free ferrites is comparatively lower than that for cobalt-based cathodes.
Titulo: Utilization of an Isovalent Doping Strategy in Cobalt-Free Ferrites for Highly Active and Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: Hence, an isovalent doping strategy is an attractive option to significantly promote the ORR activity of cobalt-free ferrites.
Titulo: Utilization of an Isovalent Doping Strategy in Cobalt-Free Ferrites for Highly Active and Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: Herein, we systematically investigate the optimal Sr2+ concentration in cobalt-free Pr0.5Ba0.5-ySryFeO3-delta (PBSF series).
Titulo: Utilization of an Isovalent Doping Strategy in Cobalt-Free Ferrites for Highly Active and Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: The replacement of Ba2+ by Sr2+ is beneficial to decrease the thermal expansion coefficient.
Titulo: Utilization of an Isovalent Doping Strategy in Cobalt-Free Ferrites for Highly Active and Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: Moreover, the Pr0.5Ba0.2Sr0.3FeO3-delta material demonstrates the highest electrical conductivity and the lowest area-specific resistance (R-p, 0.027 Omega cm(2), 700 degrees C) among the PBSF series.
Titulo: Utilization of an Isovalent Doping Strategy in Cobalt-Free Ferrites for Highly Active and Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: To elucidate the close relationship between the Rp value and the electrical conductivity in the PBSF series, distribution of relaxation time analysis and density functional theory calculations are utilized.
Titulo: Utilization of an Isovalent Doping Strategy in Cobalt-Free Ferrites for Highly Active and Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: Furthermore, outstanding cell operational durability is exhibited for 200 h.
Titulo: Utilization of an Isovalent Doping Strategy in Cobalt-Free Ferrites for Highly Active and Stable Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes
